claim.claim-text:
1. A method for searching for audio/video to gather information, including the steps of:
providing Metadata describing a audio/video having text data, image data, icon data, audio data, video data, and/or multimedia data and further including destination location information;
inputting information from the Metadata to the search system;
querying the information from the Metadata;
using text data, image data, icon data, audio data, video data, and/or multimedia data types to represent audio/video result entries;
displaying search results, as text data, image data, icon data, audio data, video data, and/or multimedia data types representing result entries related to at least one audio/video; and
using information described in the audio/video to selectively link to a call for action;
whereby the user can examine the audio/video containing information describing the objective of the audio/video in the search results list to determine if to a call to action is warranted without leaving the search results screen.

4. A method, as in claim 3, including the additional steps of:
updating information in the Metadata at a remote URL;
remotely gathering information from the Metadata on the remote web site; and
updating the database with information gathered from the Metadata under control of a client representing the remote web site;
whereby the client determines the contents of the Metadata, and determines when the database is updated with the contents of the Metadata.

6. A method, as in claim 5, including the additional steps of:
accepting one or more user initiated queries;
accepting one or more predetermined queries; and
displaying one or more audio/videos content;
wherein one or more user initiated or predetermined search criteria can be submitted to the system and related audio/videos search results can be displayed to the user.

8. A method, as in claim 7, including the additional steps of:
scheduling the display of audio/video listings by time of day;
scheduling the display of a audio/video listing by location; and
scheduling the display of audio/video listings by topic;
whereby an audio/video broadcast can be tailored to specific audiences at specific times, specific locations, and/or specific languages to achieve a call to action.

9. A method, as in claim 8, including the additional steps of:
displaying an audio/video listing by time of day;
displaying an audio/video listing by location; and
displaying an audio/video listing by topic;
whereby an audio/video user can view a message tailored to message to the user at specific times and specific locations to match the message with the audiences and languages to achieve a call to action.

10. A system for managing audio/video advertisements, and associated Metadata, comprising:
a database having video, audio, or media content specifically designed for advertising searches;
a search engine for searching the database, and producing a search results list including one or more entries representing advertisements formatted as text, image, audio, video, multimedia, and/or icon data;
display means to display the advertisements;
each advertisement further containing information describing the content of at least one call to action, wherein a call to action is a landing page, a click to call, or click to chat;
means to selectively initiate a call to action;
means to search the system with one or more user input search criteria comprising, search terms, categories and subcategories, content, and/or location data;
at least one media format is associated with the advertisement;
at least one of the audio/video advertisements is associated with one or more data sources;
the audio/video advertisements have multiple media formats for playback on multiple devices;
an advertising audio/video display window in the display means;
the system further comprises destination address data having a link address for advertising audio/video data; and
means to select the destination address data in the database and to present the advertising audio/video data to the multimedia display window;
whereby a user can selectively search the system and produce a list of results having at least one advertising audio/video result containing information describing an associated call to action in order to determine if initiating the call to action or using an optional call to action is warranted.

12. A system, as in claim 11, further comprising:
an administrative interface having means to enter Metadata comprising title, description, media URLs, landing pages, address, phone numbers, locational data, IP Address and/or call for action options and associated Metadata;
the Metadata is located in a URL consisting of a feed or Metadata associated with at least one audio/video advertisement;
the Metadata includes information describing the source location of multimedia files associated with at least one audio/video advertisement, call to action URL such as landing pages, chat, email, click to call, and/or applications;
means to update the information in a database with the information contained in the Metadata; and
a client administration site, having means to update Metadata information associated with at least one audio/video advertisement;
whereby the Metadata relates to information associated with at least one audio/video advertisement.

13. A system, as in claim 12, further comprising:
means to automatically retrieve Metadata information from a remote URL, feed or a remote server;
means to schedule the update or retrieval of data;
the Metadata is located in a URL consisting of a feed or Metadata associated to at least one audio/video advertisement;
the Metadata includes information describing the source location of multimedia files associated with at least one advertising audio/video, call to action URL such as landing pages, chat, email, and/or click to call;
means to automatically retrieve Metadata information from a media file, remote URL, feed or a remote server;
means to access remote URLs, retrieve the Metadata information associated with the remote URLs, and store the Metadata information in the system; and
means to input a feed containing Metadata information, retrieve the updated Metadata information from the feed, and store the updated Metadata information in the system.

14. A system, as in claim 13, further comprising:
means to accept one or more user initiated queries;
means to accept one or more predetermined queries; and
means to display one or more audio/video advertisements;
wherein one or more user initiated or predetermined search criteria can be submitted to the system and advertising audio/video search results can be displayed.

16. A system, as in claim 15, further comprising:
means to schedule the display of an advertising audio/video listing by time of day;
means to schedule the display of an advertising audio/video listing by location; and
means to schedule the display of an advertising audio/video listing by topic;
whereby an advertising audio/video campaign sends a message tailored to audiences at specific times and specific locations to achieve a call to action.
